Your errors are happening because you installed SFML 3.x, but the code I gave earlier was written for SFML 2.x.

SFML 3 introduced breaking API changes:

SFML 2 (old)	SFML 3 (new)
sf::VideoMode(900,700)	sf::VideoMode({900,700})
sf::Event event	std::optional<sf::Event>
pollEvent(event)	auto event = window.pollEvent()
event.type	event->is<...>()
sf::Mouse::Left	sf::Mouse::Button::Left
sf::Lines	sf::PrimitiveType::Lines

So your compiler is basically saying “this is old API.”

Instead of fighting the errors one-by-one, here is the correct SFML-3 compatible version.

Correct C++ Code (SFML 3 Compatible)
